events.name: Build Actions On Google With Dialogflow | GDG Nagpur Launch
events.description:
Hello Developers,
The wait is finally over. Google Developer Group Nagpur is excited to share and invite you to our launch meetup, brings together developers from around the Nagpur for talks, hands-on learning with tech enthusiast, and the first look at Google’s latest developer products.

For your information, GDGs are local groups of developers who are specifically interested in Google products and APIs. Each local group is called a GDG chapter and can host a variety of technical activities for developers - from just a few people getting together to watch our latest videos to large gatherings with demos and tech talks, to hackathons.

By the motive of learning new skills, We came up with an exciting topic on the day which helps you build your own chatbot using Dialogflow.

Action on Google, can easily reach and engage with users across Google. From quick commands to full conversations, Actions help you connect your content and services to users with the Google Assistant. The conference will consist of cool and vibrant events and will concentrate on "Everyday Google" and will contain talks and discussions by developers on Google technologies used in everyday life like Google Assistant, Firebase, Tensrflow, etc.

Our Speaker Mr. Ashutosh Malve (AI/ML Enthusiast, Google Developer Group Nagpur ) will deliver the talk on:

1. Building great Actions for the Google Assistant.
2. Benefits and perks of Google Assistant Developer Community Program.

Note: Keep your laptop with you.

Thanks and Regards,
GDG Nagpur Team

#GDGNagpur #GDG #WTM

In case of any query feel free to contact us at [masked]

events.name: GDG DevFest Nagpur 2019
events.description:
DevFests are community-led developer events hosted by Google Developer Groups around the globe. GDGs are focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies.

DevFest Nagpur brings together the community experts in Android, Web, Cloud and AR/VR technologies to Nagpur for 2 days of sessions, workshops and code labs. It's a multi-day full-day event with lots of learning, where the first day consists of keynotes, lightning talks, and tech sessions. The second day includes Hands-on Codelabs, Competitions and Panel discussion with an audience of professionals, entrepreneurs, and students.

**Hurry! Book your spots from https://devfest.gdgnagpur.com

Note: We won't be accepting RSVP's for DevFest, the tickets are available on the website.

events.name: Explore ML-Beginner Track
events.description:
Explore Machine Learning (ML) is a Google-sponsored program for students to get started with Machine Learning. The curriculum offers 3 tracks of machine learning content (Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced) and relies on university student facilitators to train other students.
Main motive of Explore ML is to acquire knowledge on Machine Learning as you progress from Beginner to Advanced.

*Students need to register for the workshop through the link provided: bit.ly/exploreML-VNIT
*Laptops are optional for this session.
Agenda for the event:
1. Introduction to ML.
2.ML vs Rule Based.
3.Idea to implementation.
4.History and Types of ML.
5.Neural Networks.
6.Bias in Neural Networks.
7.Uses and Limitations of Neural Networks.
8.Relating to real life applications where ML is mostly used.

Hope to see you all on Saturday:)
events.how_to_find_us: Venue: UG-2, CSE Department, VNIT Nagpur.

upcoming.name: Google Hash Code Nagpur
upcoming.description:
Hash Code is a team programming competition, organized by Google, for students and professionals around the world. You pick your team and programming language and we pick an engineering problem for you to solve. This year’s contest kicks off with an Online Qualification Round, where your team can compete from one of our Hash Code hubs. Top teams will then be invited to a Google office for the Final Round.

We have Google Hashcode Hub in Nagpur at VNIT Nagpur. Women Techmakers Nagpur is super happy to partner with the Hashcode Hub Nagpur to bring out some top coders in our community.

**Top Teams will be invited to the Final Round at Google Ireland!!**

Hashcode is given great importance by Google even through a career point of view. So what are you waiting for? Gear up for the event to bring out your coding skills by registering through https://g.co/hashcode

Select VNIT Nagpur from the list of hubs in the Judge System.
Team Limit: 2 to 4 people.
Registration Deadline: February 21st, 4:30 pm IST.
**Registration is compulsory**

Venue for the event: CRC(Class Room Complex Building), Opposite Chemical Engineering Department, VNIT Nagpur.

Come experience Hashcode and we are waiting eagerly to host you all;)
